social_posts.post_text: my most shared poems of this year (and the last few years!) ✨ thank you all for being here. i wish you an abundance of growth, healing and happiness in 2023…cause a few hurricanes for me ♥️

3 years of this poem ♥️ I’ve not edited it in that time but if my 2023 self could change one line, it would be the line about contentment never being my currency…which I now very much hope it is one day 🥹 but the rest is still very much my mood going into 2023: no settling & saying no to things that barely keep me warm.
currently unwell & in bed reading The Song of Achilles by @madeline.e.miller ♥️ book recommendations in the comments please! My favs of 2022 were ‘The Grace Year’ & ‘Atomic Habits’
i hope you trust your gut this week ♥️
when Saturn returns… 🪐 just before someone comments it: i know that astrologically, saturn is male. but…ya know. it’s a poem. thanks 🥹✌🏽
there was so much to say in this one that it needed two slides 🤍 maybe one day i’ll learn how to express myself in fewer words
